<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<title>Goldeneye (dev)</title>
		<!-- Configured by CMake (BROWSER_DEV): this stand-in is embedded in the
		     plugin instead of the real SPA bundle so the frontend can be served
		     by the Vite dev server (with hot reload) without rebuilding the
		     plugin. It just bounces the browser to the dev server. -->
		<meta http-equiv="refresh" content="0; url=http://localhost:@BROWSER_DEV_PORT@/" />
		<script>
			// Preserve any query string / hash so deep links survive the redirect.
			location.replace('http://localhost:@BROWSER_DEV_PORT@/' + location.search + location.hash);
		</script>
	</head>
	<body>
		<p>
			Redirecting to the dev server at
			<a href="http://localhost:@BROWSER_DEV_PORT@/">localhost:@BROWSER_DEV_PORT@</a>… If nothing
			happens, make sure the Vite dev server is running (<code>just dev</code>).
		</p>
	</body>
</html>
